name: Achillobator
lore: A swift and powerful dromaeosaurid theropod. Known for its large size among raptors and devastating clawed attacks.

name: Albertaceratops
lore: A ceratopsian herbivore with prominent brow horns and a wide frill. Sturdy and reliable in group defense.

name: Alioramus
lore: A slender tyrannosaurid known for its speed and agility. A fast mid-tier predator with a distinctive crested snout.

name: Allosaurus
lore: A large theropod apex predator of the Late Jurassic. Powerful jaws and strong build make it a formidable hunter.

name: Amargasaurus
lore: A small sauropod with distinctive double rows of tall spines along its neck and back, causing bleed damage to attackers.

name: Anodontosaurus
lore: A heavily armored ankylosaur with a devastating tail club capable of fracturing bones. Slow but incredibly tough.

name: Barsboldia
lore: A large hadrosaur with powerful knockback abilities. Group-oriented and capable of alerting herds to danger.

name: Camptosaurus
lore: A nimble ornithopod herbivore with exceptional stamina. One of the fastest herbivores, excelling at evasion.

name: Ceratosaurus
lore: A horned predator of the Late Jurassic. A versatile mid-tier carnivore with a balanced stat profile.

name: Concavenator
lore: A carcharodontosaurid with a distinctive hump-backed sail. Semi-aquatic capabilities give it versatility.

name: Daspletosaurus
lore: A powerful tyrannosaurid predator with crushing bite force. A heavy-hitting mid-tier apex carnivore.

name: Deinocheirus
lore: An enormous ornithomimosaur with massive claws. An excellent swimmer with bleed-inducing attacks despite being herbivorous.

name: Deinonychus
lore: An iconic raptor known for its sickle-shaped killing claw. Fast, agile and deadly in packs.

name: Eotriceratops
lore: One of the largest ceratopsians ever discovered. A massive tank with powerful charge attacks and group presence.

name: Eurhinosaurus
lore: A marine ichthyosaur with a distinctive elongated upper jaw. Dominant aquatic predator, nearly helpless on land.

name: Hatzegopteryx
lore: A colossal azhdarchid pterosaur with a massive skull. Capable of flight, making it a unique aerial predator.

name: Iguanodon
lore: A versatile ornithopod with a powerful thumb spike. Well-rounded herbivore capable of swimming efficiently.

name: Kaiwhekea
lore: A long-necked plesiosaur and apex aquatic predator. Dominates the seas but is extremely vulnerable on land.

name: Kentrosaurus
lore: A spiny stegosaur with shoulder spikes and a thagomizer tail. Its bleed-causing spines deter most predators.

name: Lambeosaurus
lore: A crested hadrosaur with a loud vocal call. Its resonating crest allows communication across vast distances.

name: Latenivenatrix
lore: The largest known troodontid. A small but incredibly fast and agile nocturnal hunter with excellent stamina.

name: Megalania
lore: A massive monitor lizard with a venomous bite. Low-profile ambush predator with semi-aquatic capabilities.

name: Metriacanthosaurus
lore: A mid-sized theropod with a distinctive spinal ridge. A fast runner with balanced combat stats.

name: Miragaia
lore: A long-necked stegosaur with impressive defensive capabilities. Uses its tail spikes to devastating effect.

name: Pachycephalosaurus
lore: The iconic dome-headed dinosaur. Uses its reinforced skull for devastating headbutt charges against predators.

name: Pycnonemosaurus
lore: A South American abelisaurid with powerful legs. One of the fastest large carnivores with a high trot speed.

name: Rhamphorhynchus
lore: A small long-tailed pterosaur. The fastest flyer in the game, excelling at aerial maneuverability and fishing.

name: Sarcosuchus
lore: A massive crocodylomorph known as the 'SuperCroc'. Apex ambush predator dominating river systems.

name: Spinosaurus
lore: The largest carnivorous dinosaur. A semi-aquatic apex predator with a massive sail and devastating bite.

name: Stegosaurus
lore: The iconic plated dinosaur with a deadly thagomizer tail. The hardest-hitting herbivore with 80 base attack damage.

name: Struthiomimus
lore: An ostrich-like ornithomimid and the fastest dinosaur in the game. Built for speed and evasion, not combat.

name: Styracosaurus
lore: A spiked ceratopsian with an impressive frill of horns. Its bleed-inducing horn attacks punish aggressive predators.

name: Suchomimus
lore: A fish-eating spinosaurid with crocodile-like jaws. A proficient swimmer and aquatic hunter.

name: Thalassodromeus
lore: A large pterosaur with a massive bony crest. Capable of sustained flight and skimming water surfaces for fish.

name: Tylosaurus
lore: A massive marine mosasaur and undisputed ruler of the prehistoric seas. Nearly immobile on land.

name: Tyrannosaurus
lore: The king of the dinosaurs. The ultimate apex predator with bone-crushing jaws and unmatched raw power.

name: Tyrannotitan
lore: A massive carcharodontosaurid with bleed-inducing bites. Rivals the T-Rex in size with superior stamina.

name: Acrocanthosaurus (Divine Beasts)
lore: A massive carcharodontosaurid from the Early Cretaceous. This Divine Beasts mod variant features a high-spined ridge along its back.

name: Ampelosaurus (Divine Beasts)
lore: A titanosaurid sauropod from the Late Cretaceous of Europe. This Divine Beasts mod variant is an armored giant.

name: Ampelosaurus (Titanus Constructus)
lore: A titanosaurid sauropod reimagined by the Titanus Constructus mod team. Features enhanced armor plating.

name: Apatosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: One of the largest land animals to ever exist. This Primordial Tyrants variant is a colossal sauropod shaking the earth with every step.

name: Argentinosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The largest dinosaur ever discovered. This Primordial Tyrants titan dwarfs all other creatures on the server.

name: Carcharodontosaurus (Divine Beasts)
lore: The 'shark-toothed lizard' of North Africa. This Divine Beasts mod variant is a fearsome apex predator with serrated teeth.

name: Carnotaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A horned abelisaurid built for speed. This Primordial Tyrants variant excels at pursuit with its powerful legs.

name: Chaos Triceratops (Akil)
lore: A heavily mutated Triceratops variant from the Akil mod. Terrifying to behold and devastating in combat.

name: Citipati (Titanus Constructus)
lore: An oviraptorid theropod from the Late Cretaceous of Mongolia. This Titanus Constructus variant features distinctive head crests.

name: Compsognathus (Divine Beasts)
lore: One of the smallest known dinosaurs. This Divine Beasts mod variant is a tiny but fierce pack hunter.

name: Deinosuchus (Divine Beasts)
lore: The 'terrible crocodile' â€” a massive alligatoroid that dwarfed modern crocodilians. A true apex aquatic ambush predator.

name: Deinosuchus (KTO)
lore: A KTO mod variant of the fearsome Deinosuchus. Rules the waterways with unmatched bite force.

name: Dilophosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A crested Early Jurassic predator. This Primordial Tyrants variant is a swift ambush hunter with dual head crests.

name: Dimetrodon (Wrath of The Goliaths)
lore: A sail-backed synapsid predator predating the dinosaurs. A formidable Permian-era hunter from the Wrath of The Goliaths mod.

name: Dracoviper Varanodon (Ex Argilla)
lore: A fantastical creature from the Ex Argilla mod. A dragon-like monitor lizard hybrid with venomous capabilities.

name: Dunkleosteus (Archetypes)
lore: A colossal armored Devonian fish with a guillotine-like bite. The ancient apex predator of prehistoric seas.

name: Edmontosaurus (Annectens) (Divine Beasts)
lore: A large hadrosaurid from the Late Cretaceous. This Divine Beasts variant of the flat-headed species is a massive herd animal.

name: Edmontosaurus (Regalis) (Divine Beasts)
lore: The crested variant of Edmontosaurus. This Divine Beasts mod species features a distinctive fleshy crest atop its skull.

name: Feline (Asylum)
lore: A mysterious feline predator from the Asylum mod. Agile, stealthy and lethal in close quarters combat.

name: Giganotosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: One of the largest terrestrial carnivores. This Primordial Tyrants apex predator rivals the T-Rex in raw power.

name: Kryptops (Divine Beasts)
lore: A small abelisaurid theropod with a face covered in keratin. A fast and ferocious mid-tier predator from the Divine Beasts mod.

name: Noviana (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A unique creature from the Primordial Tyrants mod. A versatile predator adapted to multiple environments.

name: Nyctatyrannus (IslaNycta)
lore: A nocturnal tyrannosaur from the IslaNycta mod. Adapted for hunting in darkness with enhanced senses.

name: Ocepechelon (Archetypes)
lore: A massive sea turtle from the Late Cretaceous. This Archetypes variant is a gentle giant of the prehistoric oceans.

name: Ophis (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A serpentine creature from the Primordial Tyrants mod. Stealthy and venomous, striking from the shadows.

name: Parasaurolophus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The iconic crested hadrosaur. This Primordial Tyrants variant uses its elaborate crest for resonating alarm calls.

name: Quetzalcoatlus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The largest flying animal ever. This Primordial Tyrants variant dominates the skies as the ultimate aerial predator.

name: Sachicasaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A massive pliosaur from the Early Cretaceous. This Primordial Tyrants aquatic apex predator terrorizes deep waters.

name: Smilodon (Ex Argilla)
lore: The iconic saber-toothed cat. This Ex Argilla mod variant is a swift and lethal ambush predator with signature fangs.

name: Squalicorax (Archetypes)
lore: A prehistoric crow shark from the Late Cretaceous seas. A formidable aquatic predator from the Archetypes mod.

name: Therizinosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The 'scythe lizard' with the longest claws of any known animal. This Primordial Tyrants variant wields massive 1-meter claws.

name: Titanoboa (Divine Beasts)
lore: The largest snake to ever live, reaching 12+ meters. This Divine Beasts mod variant is a massive constrictor.

name: Utahraptor (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The largest known dromaeosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Utah, USA. A stocky raptor approximately 5 meters long with a powerful skull and large arms. Its signature toe-claw is smaller than other dromaeosaurs due to its reliance on powerful jaws.

name: Velociraptor (Divine Beasts)
lore: A small but deadly dromaeosaur. This Divine Beasts variant is a feathered pack hunter with razor-sharp toe claws.

name: Yunnanosaurus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: A prosauropod from the Early Jurassic of China. This Primordial Tyrants variant is a unique early herbivore.

name: Yutyrannus (Primordial Tyrants)
lore: The largest known feathered dinosaur. This Primordial Tyrants variant is a powerful tyrannosauroid covered in filamentous plumage.

name: Zhuchengtyrannus (Divine Beasts)
lore: A massive tyrannosaurid from Late Cretaceous China. This Divine Beasts variant rivals T-Rex in size and ferocity.
